Files (verbatim copies, unmodified):
  apb_splitter.v   libfpga/busfabric/apb_splitter.v  — 1-to-N APB address decoder / demux.
  onehot_mux.v     libfpga/common/onehot_mux.v       — one-hot select mux (apb_splitter dep).
  ahbl_to_apb.v    libfpga/busfabric/ahbl_to_apb.v   — AHB-Lite->APB bridge (the DUT with the
                                                       double-transaction bug, used as a
                                                       known-bad design for the accounting proof).

Derived file (our modification of the above, same WTFPL terms):
  ahbl_to_apb_safe.sv  — ahbl_to_apb.v with the README "Proposed fix" applied (S_POSTWR/S_POSTRD
                         one-cycle bubble). The fix is documented in the reproducer
                         (/Users/roberttaylor/Code/libfpga-ahbl-to-apb-bug, README). Used as the
                         known-good design that the accounting proof must pass.

These are vendored (not a submodule) so the formal proofs in formal/splitter.sby and
formal/bridge.sby are hermetic and pinned to an exact snapshot. To refresh, re-copy from the
upstream commit above and update this NOTICE.
